--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Window Object
The global object, the following are the methods of the global object
    setInterval
    setTimeout
    alert
    confirm
    prompt
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Document Object
This is the most important object of the DOM. It holds all the important methods
that we will use.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Nodes
Each element in the DOM is called a node.

Types of Nodes
    Document Fragment
    Element Node
    Attribute node
    Comment Node
    Text Node
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Adding elements to the DOM
    element.appendChild(childNode)
    element.insertBedore(newNode)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Removing elements from the DOM
    element.removeChild(childNode)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DOM traversal
    element.parentNode
    element.childNodes
    element.children
    element.nextSibling
    element.previousSibling
    element.lastChild
    element.firstChild

    element.lastElementChild
    element.firstElementChild
    element.nextElementSibling
    element.previousElementSibling
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Replacing elements
    element.replaceChild(newChild, oldChild)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Cloning elements
    element.cloneNode(true)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Obtaining a reference of the DOM elements
    document.getElementsByTagName(tagname)
    document.getElementsById(id)
    document.getElementsByClassName(className)
    document.querySelector(selector)
    document.querySelectorAll(selector)

    Note: the nodelist returned by querySelector is not a live List
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Style

Adding styles to the element
Just assign the style to the style property of the element in question
    element.style.backgroundColor = white;

Obtaining the computed style of the element
    getComputedStyle(element, null).getPropertyValue("propertyName");
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Events

DOM Level 0 events
They are volatile and are directly used by using the onevent property of the
element.
    element.onclick = someFunction;

Standard event model



